outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Kimi
text:
I visited this outlet with my son in early October for a consultation, and unfortunately, it was a very disappointing experience. There was a Malay/Indian staff member attending to us, and I was quite taken aback by how rude and dismissive he was when I asked a few basic questions about the membership options.

I was simply trying to understand the pricing and compare it to other gyms in the area, as any parent would do before making a decision. Instead of receiving helpful information, we were met with irritated looks and a tone that made it feel like we were inconveniencing him just by asking. The way he spoke to both me and my son felt unprofessional and disrespectful, as if he was doing us a favour just by having the conversation.

I rarely leave negative reviews, but this experience left a really bad impression. When you walk into a place that promotes health and wellness, you expect a certain level of respect and basic courtesy, especially when you're considering signing up. I hope the management takes this seriously and ensures their staff are better trained in customer service. No one should be made to feel small for asking questions.

If anyone is looking to sign up for a membership I seriously advice you to think twice before signing up at this outlet.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: khrhms
text: One of the best Anytime Fitness gyms, no cap! Spacious and clean!!! Located at level 3 and right next to Lot 1 Shopping Mall. Well ventilated with air conditioning and clean/new equipment. Friendly staff. People here are also more well behaved (lol) and are socially aware. Plus points. What would make this outlet better if there‚Äôs a shower/toilet facility inside the gym. I would definitely drop by more often otw home from work these days.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Jayvinn Wong
text:
Tldr: The best AF gym in CCK, with lots of well maintained equipment, spacious layout, and clean environment.

My favourite gym in CCK, which is very well taken care of by management and members. The premises are well ventilated and pleasant smelling, without any dust lying around. When I came down in the morning, I saw a cleaner lady meticulously wiping and dusting, kudos to her! Gym members also have the habit of wiping down equipment after use. The aircon was spoilt a few months ago, but it's back now!

The equipment available is quite standard, with 2 full racks, 1 deadlift platform, 1 smith machine, and 1 hack squat machine. They also have the plate loaded low row and incline press machines, which are more unique.

One thing to note is that the toilet facilities and water cooler are outside the gym. This gym also does not have a plate loaded leg press :(

But overall, a superb gym!

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Nantha
text: The staff at AF CCK were prompt to help with my membership issue. They were able to troubleshoot by providing clear instructions to relink membership as it suddenly became inactive. Thank you üí™üèΩ ‚Ä¶

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: H
text:
Had the WORST experience ever with membership renewal. Would not recommend to renew here. Chose to sign up with this outlet to renew my membership. Even after confirming with gym ytd that my membership will begin today, the gym app and wallet pass still showed that my membership was inactive. Apparently it was let slip that the staff - forgot to update my membership. This shows that there‚Äôs 0 workflow or handover to make sure that memberships are updated properly. I‚Äôve also been informed now that there are errors to update my profile on the AF website and they are STILL unable to rectify it. Double whammy, just don‚Äôt sign up for AF membership here.

AF CCK needs to do a better job at managing memberships.

Update - matter was resolved by Dafina, she was very helpful and patient.

Further Update - Piyo took the time to reach out to me physically at the gym to share about the situation. There was handover from her to another staff about activating my membership, but it seemed that the other staff forgot to activate my gym membership. Appreciate Piyo's sincerity to address this issue directly and also very politely. Great service from Piyo.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Boom Boom
text:
I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Anytime Fitness to anyone. Joining is effortless, but leaving? That‚Äôs a whole different story. They don‚Äôt let you cancel easily‚Äîyou have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong with that email, you‚Äôre forced to keep paying. On top of that, they require a 30-day notice, which is just ridiculous. Why make it so difficult for people to leave?

The gym itself isn‚Äôt worth the stress. It‚Äôs a lot of money per month, yet the service is disappointing. The staff aren‚Äôt helpful, and I‚Äôve seen complaints about rude behaviour. A gym should be welcoming, not frustrating.

If you‚Äôre considering joining, think twice. Getting in is easy, but getting out feels like a trap.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Shrestha Saha
text: Good and spacious! less crowded in the morning. Machine availability not great ( many machines for shoulder, biceps, squat workout are not available)

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Zaifan Naim
text:
I‚Äôve been training at Anytime Fitness CCK Centre since they opened, and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with my experience.

The gym is always clean, well-maintained, and equipped with a great variety of machines and free weights. The staffs are incredibly friendly and welcoming, always ready to assist and provide helpful advice. They create a positive, motivating environment that makes every workout enjoyable.

Highly recommend this gym to anyone looking for a great fitness experience!

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Fion Chai
text: I have my PT sessions with Shafiq at AF CCKC and he is great. Tailoring each session to my individual needs and goals - whether adjusting exercises to accommodate past injuries or introducing new routines to keep things challenging. The personalized approach has made a substantial difference. Sessions with him is not boring but enjoyable. Recommend him if you‚Äôre new to gym/ want to make a change in yourself.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: chen rui ying
text:
Not happy with this place at all. Signing up was easy, but cancelling was such a hassle. They said I had to email them after my contract ended, and if they didn‚Äôt get the email, I‚Äôd have to keep paying. On top of that, I had to give one month‚Äôs notice before cancelling. Why make it so hard?

The gym costs $90++ per month, but the service is terrible. The staff are very unprofessional. The way they talk to customers makes me wonder if they have any proper training at all.

Honestly, this place is not worth the money or the trouble.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: ÈªÑÊñáÂø†
text:
Worst gym experience ever. I went to check out the place before signing up, and the staff barely paid attention to me. They seemed uninterested and acted like they were doing me a favour by answering my questions. That should have been my first red flag.

I still decided to join, thinking maybe the facilities would make up for it. Big mistake. The equipment is always occupied, and some machines are either broken or not well-maintained. The worst part? The cancellation process. It‚Äôs not straightforward at all. You have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong, you‚Äôre charged again. Plus, they require one month‚Äôs notice. It just feels like they‚Äôre making it as difficult as possible to leave.

At almost $100 per month, I expected way better. The staff are unprofessional, the gym is overcrowded, and the whole experience is just frustrating. Definitely not worth it.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: Romee TuTu
text:
While registration is easy, cancelling the membership is a nightmare. They require members to send an email after the expiry date, which is unnecessarily troublesome. If they don‚Äôt receive the email (or claim not to), you‚Äôre automatically charged for another month‚Äî$99, no less! They also have a ridiculous 30-day notice period for cancellations. Why make it so hard for members to leave?

For a gym charging this much, the service should at least be decent. Instead, the staff are unprofessional, as seen in other Google reviews where someone was body-shamed. This is unacceptable. If I wanted to donate money, I‚Äôd give it to charity, not to a gym that lacks basic accountability.

Avoid this place unless you enjoy unnecessary fees and poor service.

Changing in the common toilet was quite uncomfortable‚Äîthe wet floor made it difficult to dress and put on shoes. Hope this can be improved!

author: Jas
text:

Extremely rude staff, especially the malay guy Faris who tended to me. Only seems to be concerned with signing new members but not open to feedback.

Many friends have left the gym and went to better alternatives nearby. Will likely do the same once my contract is up.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: CY Kang
text:
Experienced an unpleasant moment. One of your staff approached me claiming that I called my friend "FAT" at the entrance which indirectly displays to the visitors that the gym has a bad environment that allows the members to address others as FAT. I truly appreciate his professionalism in his work and effort in forbidding body shaming culture in the gym, however, I had explained to the staff that the word coming out of my mouth was "FEB" (abbreviation for February) as my friend and I were discussing when were we signed up for the gym, he mentioned it was in MARCH or APRIL and I replied to him "FEB" at the entrance. Unfortunately, your staff felt I was being sarcastic and claimed that I was insulting his intelligence. Even though, he said he was not accusing me of anything and just wanted to clarify that the gym doesn't encourage such culture calling others FAT in the gym I had made my stand very clear that I didn't speak any word of FAT and I don't appreciate the way he keep repeating this to me which I had already explained over and over again. Most importantly, the staff is not apologetic at all about his accusations and put a sour face throughout our conversation.

I had paid good money for the use of the club, what I get is this shoddy treatment from your staff.

Further to this, I had emailed on Jan to enquiry on the cancellation after the minimum term. Gotten reply from the assistant manager stated to approach them after my minimum term instead of reminding that there are 30 days of notice period. Luckily this incident happened and I decided to cancel immediately after the min term and it only extend extra two days.

Gym is small with limited equipment, and there are group of customers would hog the equipment for hours, filming video of their lifts and others wouldn't have the chance to share the equipment. There is no control from the staff.

All in all, please avoid this branch and wouldn't recommend this club to others.

The friendly staff and diverse range of classes create an environment that motivates me to excel in my fitness journey. I wholeheartedly recommend it to anyone seeking a supportive and effective fitness experience.

text: Incredibly small gym for the 100+ price tag. They only have 2 squat racks that double as bench press stations. Adding a total of 10kg (5 kg per side) to your existing load was the only way then to progressively overload. Theyve since added the smaller weights, but the fact that these customer experience issues were there from the start shows a severe lack of foresight and business management skills.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre
author: JW Yeo
text:
I was a member between early 2022 to late that year. During that time, I hired a trainer by the name of Ryan Bai. He was late, rude and frequently spent more time on his phone than training people. I fired him after 3 months but already paid more than 3000 SGD in fees.

AF CCK compensated me less than 1000 SGD in membership fees but not the rest because as a third party contractor, he's not considered an AF employee.

Because of work purposes, I had no choice but to keep signing with AF in order to move around freely in Singapore. In the last year, I tried repeatedly to contact AF accounts and marketing to get the additional 2000 back in terms of membership fees.

Now as part of AF woodlands, I get chased every month when there are late fees. I also get annoyed text messages on WhatsApp everytime I'm late for fees. I paid more than 4k SGD in total for 2 years of membership. For all the money I paid, I get this sort of treatment.

I wanted to avoid trouble and simply train my body. But honestly speaking, Gymboxx, ActiveSG and SAFRA have never given me this sort of trouble. The so called gym trainer, didn't even bother to plan things or teach anything. I trained myself via youtube.
